cs.SC, cs.SE, cs.LG, cs.NA, cs.PL

This paper discusses techniques for improving the efficiency of operator overloading-based automatic differentiation schemes, which are commonly used in scientific computing and numerical analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SC (Scientific Computing and Numerical Analysis). The paper also discusses implementation details and optimization techniques, which could fall under cs.SE (Software Engineering) or cs.PL (Programming Languages). Additionally, the use of expression templates and their application to a fluid dynamics simulation could be relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
